		<description><![CDATA[Using Bitcoin technology and Google Forms with Public Results we&#8217;ve created our own fully transparent bounty program that rewards users for their participation in our non-profit. The process is simple, give us some publicity and we&#8217;ll pay you from the<span class="ellipsis">&#8230;</span><div class="read-more"><a href="http://bloodbanker.org/transparent-donation-and-bounty-reward-system-using-bitcoin-and-google">Read more &#8250;</a></div><!-- end of .read-more -->]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Using Bitcoin technology and Google Forms with Public Results we&#8217;ve created our own fully transparent bounty program that rewards users for their participation in our non-profit. The process is simple, give us some publicity and we&#8217;ll pay you from the current donation balance. At the same time, donors can see exactly what they contributed and where the money was spent. We decide how much each mention is worth and the donors can then judge the nonprofit on if that publicity is worth it.</p>
<h1>Why are we doing this?</h1>
<p>Ultimately we want to see how transparent a non-profit can be with donations by using this awesome new Bitcoin technology. We think that there are a ton of other ways that non-profits can use this model to get more complex tasks done. For example, what if a nonprofit could make confirmed mass micro-payments to the people they represent. This could enable full accountability that the money is going to the intended recipient and not a middle man.</p>
<h1>TLDR?</h1>
<p>- Full transparency for donors and charities.<br />
- Donors will see exactly where their money goes.<br />
- Donors can judge if nonprofit is making good decisions.</p>
<h1>BloodBanker Balance</h1>
<p>Here is the current balance of our Bitcoin address for this project. This address will not change and 100% of this balance will be used for only this project. (php script, might not show the actual balance on your browser)</p>
